{
  format: 1
  name: downgrade-drops-populated-field-rejected
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#evolution", "#annex-e"]
  tags: [version, replay]
  note: '''
    Attack: replay an older release over a newer instance to silently discard
    live state. §20.2: "A downgrade loads the older package and applies an
    explicit direct migration or available exact inverses. When the older shape
    cannot represent the current live values and no declared downgrade transform
    preserves them, the downgrade is rejected." The active 1.1.0 instance holds
    a populated private field `region`; the older 1.0.0 shape has no `region`
    field and declares no downgrade transform, so the current live value cannot
    be represented and the downgrade is rejected. Note the asymmetry with §20.1:
    a forward migration MAY drop a source field (it survives in history), but a
    downgrade that would lose live values is rejected. `region` is private, so
    the public boundary {id, name} is identical and does not itself force the
    outcome — the §20.2 live-value rule does.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.compat.downgrade@1.1.0"
    $model: {
      companies: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        name: "text"
        region: "text"
      }
      $public: {
        companies: { $view: ".companies { id, name }" }
      }
    }
    $data: { companies: { acme: { name: "Acme", region: "EU" } } }
  }

  steps: [
    { host_load: {
        package: {
          // older release: `region` field removed, no downgrade transform
          $liasse: 1
          $app: "t.compat.downgrade@1.0.0"
          $model: {
            companies: {
              $key: "id"
              id: "text"
              name: "text"
            }
            $public: {
              companies: { $view: ".companies { id, name }" }
            }
          }
          $data: { companies: { acme: { name: "Acme" } } }
        }
      }
      expect: {
        outcome: rejected
        violates: ["#evolution"]
        detail: "downgrade to a shape without `region` cannot represent the live value and declares no downgrade transform; rejected"
      } }
    // 1.1.0 remains active with its populated state (E.9)
    { watch: "public.companies", id: "w1",
      expect_init: { value: [ { id: "acme", name: "Acme" } ] } }
  ]
}
